   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject One Hundred Forty-five REWARD AND GRACE Scripture: Rom 4:4-5; 6:23a Wages are justly received Wages are earned through working.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Wages are a payment according to righteousness, according to the work a person renders.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Grace is freely received Grace does not require working.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Grace is freely bestowed, and not earned.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Man s sin earns him the wages of condemnation and death In the eyes of God, all of man s behavior is sin, and this behavior is man s work.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Man does no other work but to sin.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Therefore, before God we have done only the work of sin.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Man s work of sin earns the wages of death.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Thus, the Bible says, The wages of sin is death.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>God s grace is freely bestowed through the righteousness of Christ Through the righteousness of Christ, grace came to us.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>The redemption of Christ has already fulfilled the righteous requirement of God, thus enabling God to bestow grace upon us.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Grace is bestowed upon us through the redemption of Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>This is possible because His redemption reckons us righteous.</S>
   </TEXT>
